quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  33,55,"No blame on them (ladies of Prophet's household) in respect of their fathers, their sons, their brothers, their brothers' sons, their sisters' sons, their own women, or of what their right hands possess (slaves).And O ladies! Fear Allah and obey Him. Allah is indeed Witness over all things"
  33,56,"Indeed, Allah and His angels bless the Prophet. O you who believe! Bless him and greet him nicely"
  33,57,Allah has cursed those who do indeed displease Allah and His Messenger â€” cursed them in this world and the Hereafter. And He has prepared for them a disgracful punishment
  33,58,"And those who harm believing men and believing women unjustly, they become guilty of slander and manifest sin"
  33,59,"O Prophet! Tell your wives and your daughters and the women of believers to put on their outer-garments over their bodies in such a way that they are recognised and not molested.h And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is a disease and those who spread rumours and trouble in Madinah desist not, We shall certainly urge you on against them. And then they shall not be your neighbours therein but for a little while"
  33,61,"Accursed, they will be seized and slain wherever found"
  33,62,That was the way Allah dealt with those who have gone before. And you will find no change in Allah's way